      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "COUNTY COURT JUDGE (7) was solid enough when seventh last start at Newcastle, beaten 7 metres. There was plenty to like about his second at this circuit and distance prior. Peaking third-up off a let-up and a stable switch and has winning claims with even luck from the back line. RACING PAULA (10) has been competitive of late and kept the ball rolling last time when 1.2 metres from the winner in third. That made it three placings on the trot, all from this row and at this venue. Big chance to break through. THREE RIVERS NZ (1) has been coming from wider or second row draws of late so can improve plenty of late. BAT MATSON (3) will be fitter for recent racing and is much better served by today's draw so can improve.",
